{"name":"Buckler","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"shield","data":{"description":"<p>Shields come in various sizes and shapes, ranging from the small bucklers attached upon the forearm to large shields covering almost the entire body of the character bearing it. Shields are usually made from leather mounted on a frame, entirely from wood or from metal or a similar material. The most common type of shield seen in Llyhn is a medium-sized round metal shield, which covers the torso of the bearer. It is common practice in many cultures to decorate shields with ornate calligraphy, spikes or icons and charms meant to protect the bearer. Shields are used for defence, granting a bonus to the Defence Value of the user rather than reducing the damage of impacts. While bucklers do not give a Defence bonus, they can be used for blocking manoeuvres against incoming attacks in the same way as medium and small shields. Heavy wooden lids and other similar objects can be used as improvised shields but at one lower Defence modifier than its ordinary equivalent.</p>","defenceMod":0,"bulk":1,"properties":"Block"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"fp2c2PZLAh5o1khL"}
